coming together of the walking

00:11:58.490 --> 00:12:00.040
tours that I do
around San Francisco

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:01.190
where I take people out.

00:12:01.190 --> 00:12:03.909
I took a bunch of
Google people out once,

00:12:03.909 --> 00:12:05.700
right across the street
on the Embarcadero.

00:12:05.700 --> 00:12:06.650
Is that there?

00:12:06.650 --> 00:12:07.880
It's there, right?

00:12:07.880 --> 00:12:11.260
And like when you go and
you sit at the counter

00:12:11.260 --> 00:12:13.660
where I just ate lunch,
and you look down,

00:12:13.660 --> 00:12:15.860
that's where I did my
walking tour for you guys.

00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:17.910
And then along
that same shoreline

00:12:17.910 --> 00:12:20.940
I do herring tours
in the winter,

00:12:20.940 --> 00:12:22.930
because that whole
shoreline just becomes

00:12:22.930 --> 00:12:27.160
infested with Pacific herring.

00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:29.240
When they spawn, they
spawn right there,

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:32.675
and armed with a casting net,
you can throw a casting net

00:12:32.675 --> 00:12:34.660
and get your supply of
herring for the year.

00:12:34.660 --> 00:12:37.230
Most people, that would
be like three pounds.

00:12:37.230 --> 00:12:38.700
That's not mine.

00:12:38.700 --> 00:12:41.180
But in one throw when
you're fishing for herring,

00:12:41.180 --> 00:12:44.390
you can you get 25 pounds
if they're really spawning.

00:12:44.390 --> 00:12:45.370
And it's just amazing.

00:12:45.370 --> 00:12:48.157
You can do that right here.

00:12:48.157 --> 00:12:50.740
As I discussed in the book, when
you're eating small schooling

00:12:50.740 --> 00:12:55.620
fish that aren't eating in
the area where you catch them,

00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:57.720
the health risks are minimal.

00:12:57.720 --> 00:13:00.150
Herring don't live long enough
to bioaccumulate toxins.

00:13:00.150 --> 00:13:03.025
So I'm just sort of
thinking ahead here, I'm

00:13:03.025 --> 00:13:04.650
talking about catching
herring, getting

00:13:04.650 --> 00:13:05.691
your supply for the year.

00:13:05.691 --> 00:13:09.250
And I know you guys are
thinking, from there?

00:13:09.250 --> 00:13:11.500
But again, this is a
small schooling fish

00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:12.917
that lives up to
maybe five years,

00:13:12.917 --> 00:13:14.666
doesn't have time to
bioaccumulate toxins.

00:13:14.666 --> 00:13:17.050
So they're super high in omega
3s and all the good things

00:13:17.050 --> 00:13:19.180
that a fish has.

00:13:19.180 --> 00:13:21.784
Just in the winter, it's just
insane the amounts of herring.

00:13:21.784 --> 00:13:23.450
I mean literally, you
take a little net,

00:13:23.450 --> 00:13:25.200
you throw it in the
water, you pull it up,

00:13:25.200 --> 00:13:26.880
and there's 25 pounds
of flapping fish.

00:13:26.880 --> 00:13:28.360
I used to have a
video of myself,

00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:30.377
and I showed you guys
that one of my talks here.

00:13:30.377 --> 00:13:32.710
I held up the cell and everybody
was just-- because it's

00:13:32.710 --> 00:13:36.570
right by the arrow,
the bow and arrow,

00:13:36.570 --> 00:13:39.790
like right on the other side of
that right where the water is

00:13:39.790 --> 00:13:42.190
just-- throwing that in
the water in the winter,

00:13:42.190 --> 00:13:43.280
on certain days.

00:13:43.280 --> 00:13:46.360
Anyway, I don't know why
I'm going there, but--

00:13:46.360 --> 00:13:47.566
I do these tours.

00:13:47.566 --> 00:13:49.440
And this was the
culmination of all the stuff

00:13:49.440 --> 00:13:55.550
I talk about on my tours, plus
little anecdotes and things.

00:13:55.550 --> 00:13:57.680
One of my favorite chapters
to read from in here

00:13:57.680 --> 00:14:00.200
is my bait chapter.

