00:42:37.450 --> 00:42:39.866
I used to work for the fish
and game department explaining

00:42:39.866 --> 00:42:41.230
all the rules and regulations.

00:42:41.230 --> 00:42:42.780
And I'm back there now.

00:42:42.780 --> 00:42:47.800
But in any case, yes, and so
the seaweeds and the clams.

00:42:47.800 --> 00:42:54.130
Some of the fishing stuff, if
you have some basis in fishing,

00:42:54.130 --> 00:42:58.730
I think you'll be fine.

00:42:58.730 --> 00:43:01.140
But if you have no basis
at all in catching fish,

00:43:01.140 --> 00:43:06.810
like you've never gone
like this, if you've never

00:43:06.810 --> 00:43:12.780
done that before, then there's
a whole chapter on poke poling.

00:43:12.780 --> 00:43:15.740
Poke poling is a
technique that was

00:43:15.740 --> 00:43:18.240
used by Native Americans
along this coast for thousands

00:43:18.240 --> 00:43:21.190
of years, I think, at least.

00:43:21.190 --> 00:43:26.810
And you can catch a lot of
fish by just taking a stick.

00:43:26.810 --> 00:43:29.580
Now the modern
adaptation of this stick

00:43:29.580 --> 00:43:34.220
is you take the stick, you take
a wire hanger from your closet.

00:43:34.220 --> 00:43:36.780
You unravel it, put a
little loop in the end,

00:43:36.780 --> 00:43:39.250
tie some line onto it,
put a hook on the line.

00:43:39.250 --> 00:43:40.970
So you've got a stick.

00:43:40.970 --> 00:43:44.900
Bamboo is great, a bamboo
stick, wire hanger,

00:43:44.900 --> 00:43:47.630
loop in the wire
hanger at the bottom.

00:43:47.630 --> 00:43:49.070
Wire hanger is taped.

00:43:49.070 --> 00:43:55.540
So stick, tape, wire
hanger, loop, line, hook.

00:43:55.540 --> 00:43:58.150
Onto that hook, put a
little piece of squid.

00:43:58.150 --> 00:44:00.890
Go to any fish market in the Bay
Area and buy a pound of squid

00:44:00.890 --> 00:44:05.080
for $2.69.

00:44:05.080 --> 00:44:06.690
And then walk out at low tide.

00:44:06.690 --> 00:44:10.060
And everywhere you see a
rock that comes together

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:13.900
with another rock or a
hole or a crack, stick

00:44:13.900 --> 00:44:17.970
that gently into the--
the sexual innuendo here

00:44:17.970 --> 00:44:19.510
is through the roof.

00:44:19.510 --> 00:44:24.730
You stick your
stick into the hole,

00:44:24.730 --> 00:44:30.080
and then as you go like this
and you kind of, like, do this,

00:44:30.080 --> 00:44:32.390
the fish that live in the
holes between the rocks

00:44:32.390 --> 00:44:34.820
will come up and bite the
hook and you pull them out

00:44:34.820 --> 00:44:35.680
of the hole.

00:44:35.680 --> 00:44:38.385
And that requires none
of this, [WHOOSH].

00:44:38.385 --> 00:44:40.760
And it's a very good way to
go along the California coast

00:44:40.760 --> 00:44:45.320
and get your own fish.

00:44:45.320 --> 00:44:47.050
So hopefully that
answers your question.

00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:49.550
And that's a very
wonderful technique

00:44:49.550 --> 00:44:52.631
for beginning fishermen to use,
because you'll catch stuff.

00:44:52.631 --> 00:44:54.630
And all you have to do
is tie a couple of knots.

00:44:54.630 --> 00:44:55.860
And that's it.

